In this article, President Barack Obama sends a message to Congress and publishes a Federal Register notice concerning Syria. He states that the national emergency with respect to the actions of the Government of Syria will continue beyond May 11, 2009. The President cites Syria's support for terrorism, pursuit of weapons of mass destruction and missile programs, and undermining of U.S. and international efforts in Iraq as reasons for the continuing national emergency. He determines that it is necessary to maintain the sanctions in place to address this threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. The notice is published in accordance with Section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act.